<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>International&#174; T 444E Diesel Engine Service, Model Year 1994 - 1998 - TURBOCHARGER - Inspection - Check
        Wastegate Actuator (High Torque Model)
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc graphiccount="1">
        <title>Check Wastegate Actuator (High Torque Model)</title>
        <figure id="f1200230" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figeg6/eg6732.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="248px" box="yes"/>
            <caption>Checking the Wastegate Actuator</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Magnetic Base</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Air Pressure Regulator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wastegate Actuator Shaft</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Wastegate Actuator</callout1>
                <callout1 type="arabic">Dial Indicator</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the turbocharger on a flat surface. Position a dial indicator with a magnetic base
                next to the turbocharger. Place the tip of the dial indicator inline and at the end of the wastegate
                actuator shaft. Reset the indicator needle to zero.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Connect an air hose to a shop air pressure regulator. Adjust the air pressure to 117.2 - 131
                kPa (17-19 psi). Temporarily close off the air supply to let the air pressure gauge return to zero.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use a hose and appropriate fittings to connect the regulated shop air hose to the wastegate
                actuator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Gradually apply shop air pressure to achieve 117.2 - 131 kPa (17-19 psi) of air pressure.
                Record the reading on the dial indicator.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If the reading does not meet specifications, the wastegate actuator must be replaced.</para>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
